From 9d10c3238e702317f03605f325ca3c57bbc57924 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Sep 2025 15:19:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k: Fix missing PPE VP table cleanup on AP
 VLAN interface removal

Currently, AP VLAN interface teardown was incorrectly referencing ahvif
instead of vlan_master_ahvif during link cleanup. As a result, the PPE VP
table entry associated with it is not removed, leaving stale entries.

Update the link dereference to use vlan_master_ahvif to ensure the
correct link context is used. This will proper cleanup the PPE VP
table.

Patch-Dependency:
	0337-10-QSDK-DP-wifi-Enable-DS-support-for-WDS-AP_VLAN-inter.patch
Fixes:
	I56018d1a5bb (QSDK: DP: wifi: Package upgrade changes for datapath 
		      accelerator features.)

Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -16486,7 +16486,7 @@ void ath12k_mac_op_remove_interface(stru
 		 * free the allocated cache.
 		 */
 		ath12k_ahvif_put_link_cache(ahvif, link_id);
-		arvif = wiphy_dereference(hw->wiphy, ahvif->link[link_id]);
+		arvif = wiphy_dereference(hw->wiphy, vlan_master_ahvif->link[link_id]);
 		if (!arvif || !arvif->is_created)
 			continue;
 
